reviewText: This one was entertaining, though many of the characters were over-the-top.  I bought this to watch with my 12 year old daughter.  We were looking for fluff and that's what we got, so if that's your goal, you'll enjoy it.  My daughter enjoyed it more than I did.
Title: Nearlyweds

reviewText: My wife and I like watching Hallmark movies and this movie was another great one that will be coming out soon. You will get some great snafus and humorous moments. There were so many comedies of errors throughout the movie, it left me with a smile on my face and thoroughly entertained. The actors did a great job portraying their characters and making them believable and likable. Overall, this was a fun movie for the whole family!*I received this for review - all opinions are my own*
Title: Nearlyweds

reviewText: This movie Nearlyweds starring Danielle Panabaker, Jessica Parker Kennedy and Britt Irvin and Naomi Judd. This movie is about three best friends, named Erin (Danielle Panabaker), Casey (Jessica Parker Kennedy) and Stella (Britt Irvin) who get married in the same month. The three girls all thought they were getting happily ever after.  One day a letter came out to all three girls saying that the three girls are not married because some important papers were not filed. When the girls first read the letters they are afraid of telling their husbands because they think they will not marry them again because there are some bumps in the road with their marriages. Watch this movie to see if Erin, Casey and Stella ever get married for real. This movie is really cute! I hope you enjoy it!!
